A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Task Force on the Establishment of a State Park Dedicated to Veterans’ Care
3 FOR the purpose of establishing the Task Force on the Establishment of a State Park
4 Dedicated to Veterans’ Care to study issues and estimate costs related to the
5 establishment of a State park dedicated to providing recreational opportunities and
6 therapeutic services to veterans; and generally relating to the Task Force on the
7 Establishment of a State Park Dedicated to Veterans’ Care.
8 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
9 That:
10 (a) There is a Task Force on the Establishment of a State Park Dedicated to
11 Veterans’ Care.
12 (b) (1) The Task Force shall include the following members:
13 (i) one member of the Senate of Maryland, appointed by the
14 President of the Senate;
15 (ii) one member of the House of Delegates, appointed by the Speaker
16 of the House;
17 (iii) the Secretary of Natural Resources, or the Secretary’s designee;
18 (iv) the Secretary of Veterans and Military Families, or the
19 Secretary’s designee;
20 (v) the Director of the Maryland Park Service, or the Director’s
21 designee;
