1 (vi) one county commissioner of Washington County, appointed by
2 the President of the Washington County Board of Commissioners;
3 (vii) the County Administrator of Washington County, or the County
4 Administrator’s designee;
5 (viii) the following members, appointed by the Secretary of Natural
6 Resources:
7 1. one representative of the Hagerstown–Washington
8 County Convention and Visitors Bureau;
9 2. one representative of an organization that provides
10 therapeutic services to veterans; and
11 3. the owner of land located in the Southern portion of
12 Washington County that has been proposed for transfer to the State for the purpose of
13 establishing a State park dedicated to veterans’ care; and
14 (ix) one resident from legislative district 2 in Washington County.
15 (2) In addition to the members specified under paragraph (1) of this
16 subsection, the Secretary of Natural Resources may invite a representative of the National
17 Park Service and any other relevant stakeholders to serve as members of the Task Force.
18 (c) The Secretary of Natural Resources shall designate the chair of the Task
19 Force.
20 (d) The Department of Natural Resources shall provide staff for the Task Force.
21 (e) A member of the Task Force:
22 (1) may not receive compensation as a member of the Task Force; but
23 (2) is entitled to reimbursement for expenses under the Standard State
24 Travel Regulations, as provided in the State budget.
25 (f) The Task Force shall:
26 (1) study issues and estimate costs related to the establishment of a State
27 park dedicated to providing recreational opportunities and therapeutic services to veterans;
28 (2) make recommendations regarding:
29 (i) services and amenities to be provided by the park;

